    "title":  "Ionrift Respite",
    "description":  "Structured long rest and short rest phases for DnD 5e and Pathfinder 2e. Replaces the default rest dialog with a guided camping flow. Camp deploys onto the scene with a campfire, workbench, weapon rack, and cooking station. Players self-serve their downtime activities: identifying magic items, attuning gear, copying spells, crafting arrows, cooking meals with homebrew recipes per profession, foraging terrain-specific ingredients, and more. The GM runs terrain-driven wilderness encounters and random events across 6 terrains with multiple outcome tiers. Chef feat support, a camp fuel table, and player-rolled travel loot round out the experience. Built for tables that want immersive camping without the bookkeeping.",
